Description: Shoulder sherd of Milesian pottery closed vessel, oinochoe or amphora; exterior: animal frieze; on the left, sphinx (face, front legs preserved) facing right with left paw raised towards a goat or deer (right hind leg preserved) running to the right; triangle and rhomb as filling ornament; below, two lines and a band of key maeander.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.927)
Schlotzhauer 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus Naukratis (p. 91-100, Nau 34, pl. 8e-f)
